Problem: First Matching Character From Both Ends
Topic: Strings, Two Pointers
Difficulty: Easy

Approach:
Traverse the string from the beginning and compare each character with its corresponding character from the end. Return the first index where both characters match.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    int firstMatchingIndex(string s) {
        int n=s.length();
        
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                if(s[i]==s[n-i-1]){
                    return i;
                }
            }
        return -1;
    }
};
